    "slug": "4-unique-call-to-actions-to-test-on-your-nonprofits-website",
    "link": "https://www.nptechforgood.com/2022/10/25/4-unique-call-to-actions-to-test-on-your-nonprofits-website/",
    "title": {
      "rendered": "4 Unique Call-to-Actions to Test on Your Nonprofit&#8217;s Website"
    },
    "content": {
      "rendered": "<p><b>By\u00a0<a href=\"http://www.nptechforgood.com/heather-mansfield/\">Heather Mansfield</a>, founder and editor-in-chief of Nonprofit Tech for Good</b></p>\n<hr />\n<p>According to the <a href=\"https://mrbenchmarks.com/\">2022 M+R Benchmarks Report</a>, nonprofits pay an average of $3.31 to secure a lead [i.e., capture an email address] through digital advertising. Most small and medium-sized nonprofits can&#8217;t afford to experiment with digital advertising for lead generation, but there are other means of securing new leads for a fraction of the cost \u2013 namely, your nonprofit&#8217;s website empowered with any of the following unique call-to-actions (CTAs).</p>\n<h2>1) Top bar opt-ins and links</h2>\n<p>The red newsletter opt-in top bar on Nonprofit Tech for Good is the best-performing newsletter CTA on our website. Over the last six months, the top bar has resulted in 973 new contacts compared to 476 new contacts from a (now removed) popup form that appeared 20 seconds after load to non-subscribers. At a cost of $13.99 a month, <a href=\"https://www.mailmunch.com/\">MailMunch</a> is an exceptional value for adding top bars and other CTAs to your website. See also <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/\">OptinMonster</a>.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Email-Newsletter-Top-Bar-Opt-In.jpg\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-34071\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Email-Newsletter-Top-Bar-Opt-In.jpg?resize=800%2C474\" alt=\"\" width=\"800\" height=\"474\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Email-Newsletter-Top-Bar-Opt-In.jpg?w=800&amp;ssl=1 800w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Email-Newsletter-Top-Bar-Opt-In.jpg?resize=300%2C178&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Email-Newsletter-Top-Bar-Opt-In.jpg?resize=768%2C455&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Email-Newsletter-Top-Bar-Opt-In.jpg?resize=50%2C30&amp;ssl=1 50w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\" /></a></p>\n<p>Top bars can also be links to pages on your website. For example, the <a href=\"https://www.nature.org/en-us/\">Nature Conservancy uses a maroon top bar</a> to send visitors prompted by TV ads to their monthly giving donation page.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Nature-Conservancy-Top-Bar.jpg\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-34070\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Nature-Conservancy-Top-Bar.jpg?resize=800%2C384\" alt=\"\" width=\"800\" height=\"384\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Nature-Conservancy-Top-Bar.jpg?w=800&amp;ssl=1 800w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Nature-Conservancy-Top-Bar.jpg?resize=300%2C144&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Nature-Conservancy-Top-Bar.jpg?resize=768%2C369&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Nature-Conservancy-Top-Bar.jpg?resize=50%2C24&amp;ssl=1 50w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\" /></a></p>\n<h2>2) Slide-in &#8220;Donate&#8221; prompts</h2>\n<p>Approximately 20 seconds after landing on the website for the <a href=\"https://www.ccalliance.org/\">Colorectal Cancer Alliance website</a>, a small &#8220;Donate&#8221; popup slides in featuring a recent donation. Clever!</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://www.ccalliance.org/\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-34131 size-full\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Cancer-Alliance-Fundraising-e1666645360644.jpg?resize=800%2C384\" alt=\"\" width=\"800\" height=\"384\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Cancer-Alliance-Fundraising-e1666645360644.jpg?w=800&amp;ssl=1 800w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Cancer-Alliance-Fundraising-e1666645360644.jpg?resize=300%2C144&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Cancer-Alliance-Fundraising-e1666645360644.jpg?resize=768%2C369&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Cancer-Alliance-Fundraising-e1666645360644.jpg?resize=50%2C24&amp;ssl=1 50w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\" /></a></p>\n<h2>3) Embedded opt-ins and donation forms in blog and news content</h2>\n<p>A growing trend is to add large, visually prominent CTAs to the body of blog posts and news articles approximately halfway down the page. Nonprofit Tech for Good embeds a newsletter opt-in at the bottom of each post (see below) which surprisingly results in 5-10 new subscribers daily.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>1) Embedded newsletter opt-in on the <a href=\"https://www.themarshallproject.org/2020/08/13/con-air-is-spreading-covid-19-all-over-the-federal-prison-system\">Marshall Project blog</a></strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://www.themarshallproject.org/2020/08/13/con-air-is-spreading-covid-19-all-over-the-federal-prison-system\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter wp-image-27036 size-full\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/Marshall-Project.jpg?resize=733%2C705\" alt=\"Email newsletter sign up form embedded in the middle of a nonprofit's blog post.\" width=\"733\" height=\"705\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/Marshall-Project.jpg?w=733&amp;ssl=1 733w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/Marshall-Project.jpg?resize=300%2C289&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 733px) 100vw, 733px\" /></a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>2) Embedded donation form on the <a href=\"https://www.hrw.org/news/2020/08/18/carpet-bodies-one-womans-ordeal-detention-belarus\">Human Rights Watch blog</a></strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://www.hrw.org/news/2020/08/18/carpet-bodies-one-womans-ordeal-detention-belarus\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter wp-image-27043 size-full\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/Human-Rights-Watch.jpg?resize=735%2C560\" alt=\"A donation form embedded in the middle of blog post.\" width=\"735\" height=\"560\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/Human-Rights-Watch.jpg?w=735&amp;ssl=1 735w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/Human-Rights-Watch.jpg?resize=300%2C229&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 735px) 100vw, 735px\" /></a></p>\n<h2>4) Top of homepage donation forms</h2>\n<p>The <a href=\"https://www.aclu.org/\">ACLU has had a donation form featured at the top of their homepage</a> for almost a year and while there is no public data on its performance, the form must be performing well or it would have been removed months ago. The concept is worth experimenting with! It&#8217;s worth noting that after you click the &#8220;X&#8221; to close the form, it is no longer visible for 24 hours.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://www.aclu.org/\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-34100\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Top-Bar-Donation-Form.jpg?resize=800%2C716\" alt=\"\" width=\"800\" height=\"716\" /></a></p>\n<hr />\n<h2><strong>Earn a Certificate in Social Media Marketing &amp; Fundraising!</strong></h2>\n<p>Our new\u00a0<a href=\"http://www.nptechforgood.com/101-best-practices/earn-a-certificate-in-social-media-marketing-fundraising-from-nonprofit-tech-for-good/\" rel=\"noopener\" data-cke-saved-href=\"http://www.nptechforgood.com/earn-a-certificate-in-digital-marketing-fundraising-from-nonprofit-tech-for-good/\">Certificate in Social Media Marketing &amp; Fundraising</a> program covers the fundamentals of social media marketing and fundraising for nonprofits. Participants will learn how to create and maintain a content strategy, current best practices for the top-performing social media sites, and how to be an early adopter of emerging social media trends.</p>\n<p>Based on\u00a0<a href=\"http://www.nptechforgood.com/101-best-practices/\"><em>101 Digital Marketing &amp; Fundraising Best Practices for Nonprofits</em></a>, the certificate program requires the completion of four webinars. The program only costs $100 USD so that nonprofit professionals worldwide can earn the certificate without having to make a significant financial investment.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.nptechforgood.com/101-best-practices/earn-a-certificate-in-social-media-marketing-fundraising-from-nonprofit-tech-for-good/\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-34243 size-full\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/2023-Social-Media-Marketing-Certificate.png?resize=800%2C628\" alt=\"\" width=\"800\" height=\"628\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/2023-Social-Media-Marketing-Certificate.png?w=800&amp;ssl=1 800w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/2023-Social-Media-Marketing-Certificate.png?resize=300%2C236&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/2023-Social-Media-Marketing-Certificate.png?resize=768%2C603&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/2023-Social-Media-Marketing-Certificate.png?resize=50%2C39&amp;ssl=1 50w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\" /></a></p>\n<hr />\n<div style=\"background-color: #8362ae; padding: 4px;\"></div>\n<div style=\"background-color: #efebeb; padding: 5px;\">\n<h2><strong> \u25ba </strong><b>About the Author</b></h2>\n</div>\n<div style=\"background-color: #efebeb; padding: 5px;\"><a style=\"color: #8362ae;\" href=\"http://www.nptechforgood.com/heather-mansfield/\">Heather Mansfield</a> is the founder and editor-in-chief of Nonprofit Tech for Good. Fueled by a strong passion for the Internet, Heather spends her days (and some nights) helping nonprofits, charities, and NGOs worldwide utilize the internet as a tool for social good.</div>\n<hr />\n",
